#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:1
msgid "Backend Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:3
msgid ""
"The backend is a Node.js/Express TypeScript API. It sits between the React "
"frontend and two external services: TriplyDB (SPARQL knowledge graph) and "
"Operaton (DMN execution engine). Its responsibilities are SPARQL querying, "
"DMN chain orchestration, variable mapping between chain steps, and proxying "
"dynamic TriplyDB endpoint calls."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:7
msgid "API versioning"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:9
msgid ""
"All endpoints follow `/v1/*`. Legacy `/api/*` endpoints exist with "
"`Deprecation` response headers for backward compatibility. The version is "
"included in every response via the `API-Version` header, following Dutch "
"Government API Design Rules API-20 and API-57."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:13
msgid "Endpoints"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:15
msgid "Health"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:17
msgid "GET /v1/health"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:21
msgid ""
"Returns service health including TriplyDB and Operaton latency checks. Used "
"by CI/CD pipelines and the frontend status indicator."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:23
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"name\": \"Linked Data Explorer Backend\",\n"
"  \"version\": \"0.4.0\",\n"
"  \"environment\": \"production\",\n"
"  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n"
"  \"uptime\": 3600,\n"
"  \"services\": {\n"
"    \"triplydb\": { \"status\": \"up\", \"latency\": 145 },\n"
"    \"operaton\": { \"status\": \"up\", \"latency\": 98 }\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:37
msgid "DMN discovery"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:39
msgid "GET /v1/dmns?endpoint={sparql_endpoint_url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:43
msgid ""
"Queries TriplyDB for all `cprmv:DecisionModel` resources at the given "
"endpoint. Returns models with full variable lists and governance/vendor "
"metadata. Cached per endpoint for 5 minutes."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:45
msgid "GET /v1/dmns/:identifier?endpoint={url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:49
msgid "Returns full metadata for a single DMN by its `dct:identifier` value."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:51
msgid "GET /v1/dmns/enhanced-chain-links?endpoint={url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:55
msgid ""
"Returns all chain links including both exact identifier matches and semantic "
"`skos:exactMatch` matches. Each link includes a `matchType` field: "
"`\"exact\"`, `\"semantic\"`, or `\"both\"`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:57
msgid "GET /v1/dmns/semantic-equivalences?endpoint={url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:61
msgid ""
"Returns all variable pairs from different DMNs that share a "
"`skos:exactMatch` concept URI."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:63
msgid "GET /v1/dmns/cycles?endpoint={url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:67
msgid ""
"Returns circular dependencies detected via semantic links (3-hop traversal)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:69
msgid "Chain discovery"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:71
msgid "GET /v1/chains?endpoint={url}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:75
msgid ""
"Returns all DMN pairs where an output variable of one model matches an input "
"variable of another by exact identifier."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:77
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\backend.md:77"
msgid "Chain execution"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:79
msgid "POST /v1/chains/execute"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:83
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\backend.md:83"
msgid "Request body:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:85
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"chain\": [\"SVB_LeeftijdsInformatie\", "
"\"SZW_BijstandsnormInformatie\"],\n"
"  \"inputs\": { \"geboortedatum\": \"1960-01-01\" },\n"
"  \"endpoint\": \"https://api.open-regels.triply.cc/...\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:93
msgid ""
"Executes the chain sequentially, flattening outputs into inputs between "
"steps. Returns per-step results and combined final output."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:95
msgid "POST /v1/chains/execute/heusdenpas"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:99
msgid ""
"Convenience endpoint for the fixed three-step Heusdenpas chain with "
"production test data. Target execution time: <1000ms. See [API Reference]{1} "
"for the full request/response."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:101
msgid "POST /v1/chains/export"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:105
msgid ""
"Generates a DRD XML file from a chain and deploys it to Operaton. See [DRD "
"Generation]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:107
msgid "eDOCS"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:109
msgid ""
"GET  /v1/edocs/status\n"
"POST /v1/edocs/workspaces/ensure\n"
"POST /v1/edocs/documents\n"
"GET  /v1/edocs/workspaces/:workspaceId/documents"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:116
msgid ""
"Integrates with the OpenText eDOCS document management system. Used by the "
"RIP Phase 1 process to create project workspaces and file documents. In stub "
"mode (`EDOCS_STUB_MODE=true`, default) all methods return realistic fake "
"responses so the process runs end-to-end before a live eDOCS server is "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:118
msgid ""
"See [eDOCS Integration]{1} and the [API Reference]{2} for request/response "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:120
msgid "TriplyDB proxy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:122
msgid "POST /v1/triplydb/query"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:126
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\backend.md:126"
msgid "Request body:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:128
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"endpoint\": \"https://api.open-regels.triply.cc/...\",\n"
"  \"query\": \"SELECT ?s ?p ?o WHERE { ?s ?p ?o } LIMIT 5\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:135
msgid ""
"Proxies a SPARQL query to any TriplyDB endpoint, bypassing CORS "
"restrictions. Used by the frontend Query Editor for dynamic endpoint support."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:139
msgid "Asset storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:140
msgid ""
"GET    /v1/assets/bpmn\n"
"POST   /v1/assets/bpmn\n"
"DELETE /v1/assets/bpmn/:id\n"
"GET    /v1/assets/bpmn/by-bpmn-id/:bpmnProcessId\n"
"\n"
"GET    /v1/assets/forms\n"
"POST   /v1/assets/forms\n"
"DELETE /v1/assets/forms/:id\n"
"\n"
"GET    /v1/assets/documents\n"
"POST   /v1/assets/documents\n"
"DELETE /v1/assets/documents/:id"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:155
msgid ""
"Persists BPMN processes, form schemas, and document templates to PostgreSQL. "
"All routes return `503 DB_NOT_CONFIGURED` when `DATABASE_URL` is absent. See "
"[Asset Storage]{1} for the service architecture and [API Reference]{2} for "
"full request/response documentation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:159
msgid "Database"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:161
msgid ""
"The backend connects to a PostgreSQL database via a `pg.Pool`. The pool is "
"initialised in `src/db/pool.ts` when `DATABASE_URL` is present in the "
"environment. If the variable is absent, `pool` is `null` and all asset "
"endpoints respond with `503`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:163
msgid ""
"Schema migrations run automatically on startup via `migrate()` in `src/db/"
"migrate.ts`, called from `startServer()` before `app.listen()`. The "
"migration is idempotent (`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:164
msgid ""
"src/db/\n"
"├── pool.ts       — pg.Pool initialisation, error listener, null-if-"
"unconfigured guard\n"
"└── migrate.ts    — idempotent DDL: process_definitions, form_schemas, "
"document_templates"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:170
msgid "See [PostgreSQL Deployment]{1} for Azure provisioning."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:174
msgid "SPARQL service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:176
msgid ""
"`sparql.service.ts` builds and executes all SPARQL queries against TriplyDB. "
"Key functions:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:178
msgid ""
"findAllDmns(endpoint: string): Promise<DmnModel[]>\n"
"findEnhancedChainLinks(endpoint: string): Promise<EnhancedChainLink[]>\n"
"findSemanticEquivalences(endpoint: string): Promise<SemanticEquivalence[]>"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:184
msgid ""
"The `findEnhancedChainLinks` query uses a `BIND(IF(...))` pattern to "
"categorise each link as `exact`, `semantic`, or `both`, then expands `both` "
"entries into two separate records post-query. This is the mechanism "
"described in [Enhanced Validation]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:188
msgid "Orchestration service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:190
msgid "`orchestration.service.ts` executes sequential chains:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:192
msgid "Fetch DMN metadata for each step from the SPARQL service (cached)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:193
msgid "For the first step, use the user-supplied inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:194
msgid "For each subsequent step, build inputs by:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:194
msgid "Flattening all previous step outputs into a single map"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:194
msgid ""
"For semantic matches: rename output variable keys to match the expected "
"input identifiers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:194
msgid "Merge with any additional user-supplied inputs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:198
msgid "Call `operaton.service.ts` for each step"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:199
msgid "Accumulate results"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:201
msgid ""
"Variable flattening means a semantic chain like `heeftJuisteLeeftijd → "
"leeftijd_requirement` is transparently bridged — the output value is passed "
"under the input's expected key."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:205
msgid "Operaton service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:207
msgid "`operaton.service.ts` calls the Operaton REST API:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:209
msgid "POST {OPERATON_BASE_URL}/decision-definition/key/{decisionRef}/evaluate"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:213
msgid "Request payload maps to Operaton's variable format:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:215
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"variables\": {\n"
"    \"geboortedatum\": { \"value\": \"1960-01-01\", \"type\": \"String\" }\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:223
msgid ""
"For DRD execution, the same endpoint is used with the DRD entry-point "
"identifier. Operaton handles internal decision dependency evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:227
msgid "eDOCS service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:229
msgid ""
"`edocs.service.ts` wraps the OpenText eDOCS REST API. It authenticates once "
"via `POST /connect`, caches the `X-DM-DST` session token, and re-"
"authenticates automatically on `401`/`403`. Key methods:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:231
msgid ""
"ensureWorkspace(projectNumber: string, projectName: string): "
"Promise<EdocsWorkspaceResult>\n"
"uploadDocument(workspaceId: string, filename: string, contentBase64: string, "
"metadata: EdocsDocumentMetadata): Promise<EdocsDocumentResult>\n"
"getWorkspaceDocuments(workspaceId: string): Promise<...>\n"
"healthCheck(): Promise<{ status: 'up' | 'down' | 'stub' }>"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:238
msgid ""
"When `EDOCS_STUB_MODE=true`, all methods return realistic fake data and log "
"what they would have done. The stub is transparent to all callers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:242
msgid "External task worker"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:244
msgid ""
"`externalTaskWorker.service.ts` polls Operaton's external task API (`POST /"
"external-task/fetchAndLock`) using long-polling (`asyncResponseTimeout: 20 "
"000 ms`). It handles two topics:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "Topic"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "Reads"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "Writes"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "`rip-edocs-workspace`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "`projectNumber`, `projectName`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "`edocsWorkspaceId`, `edocsWorkspaceName`, `edocsWorkspaceCreated`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "`rip-edocs-document`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid ""
"`edocsWorkspaceId`, `documentTemplateId`, `edocsDocumentVariableName`, + "
"template variables"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:246
msgid "`<edocsDocumentVariableName>` (e.g. `edocsIntakeReportId`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:251
msgid ""
"`documentTemplateId` and `edocsDocumentVariableName` are injected per "
"ServiceTask via `camunda:inputParameter` in the BPMN, making the single "
"topic handler reusable across all three document upload steps in the RIP "
"Phase 1 process."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:253
msgid ""
"The worker starts inside the `app.listen()` callback and stops in both "
"`SIGTERM` and `SIGINT` handlers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:257
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:259
msgid ""
"Winston structured logging with JSON output. All service calls log at "
"`[INFO]` level with context (endpoint, query length, result count, latency). "
"Errors log at `[ERROR]` with stack traces. Log level is configurable via "
"`LOG_LEVEL` environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:263
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:265
msgid ""
"A central `errorHandler.ts` middleware catches unhandled errors and returns "
"standardised JSON error responses with appropriate HTTP status codes. SPARQL "
"and Operaton errors are wrapped with descriptive messages before being "
"returned to the frontend. No sensitive data is included in error responses."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:269
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cbackend.md:271
msgid "**Targets:**"
msgstr ""

